  <preparation>Heat the oil and fry the onion, bell pepper, garlic and fresh chili for 5 minutes.  Stir in chili powder, ground cumin and stir before adding stock or water, epazoe and a grinding of pepper.  Cook for 50 minutes, addng more water if necessary.  

When beans are tender, salt them to taste.  Mash 1/4 of the mixture and return to pan.  Add sugar and serve hot with cheese sprinkled on top.   Serve with, e.g., long-grain rice.</preparation>
